notes=Mount Sniktau is the massive peak that catches skiers' eyes when they are driving west on Interstate 70 at mile marker 224 near the town of Silver Plume. The mountain is viewed by many, climbed by many, but skied from the summit to I-70 by few. Sniktau is a highly accessible mountain as it is connected directly to the popular Loveland Pass. The climb from Loveland Pass to the summit of Mount Sniktau is a good beginner mountaineering climb. The challenge of skiing on Sniktau is not the ascent, the challenge 
